<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08368</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT STRENGTHENING THE REGULATION OF EMPLOYMENT OF FOREIGN NATIONALS AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE ARTICLES 40, 41 AND 42 OF PRESIDENTIAL DECREE NO. 442, AS AMENDED, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE "LABOR CODE OF THE PHILIPPINES"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Strengthening The Regulation Of Employment Of Foreign Nationals, Amending For The Purpose Articles 40, 41 And 42 Of Presidential Decree No. 442, As Amended, Otherwise Known As The " Labor Code Of The Philippines " </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Mandates that ALL NON-RESIDENT FOREIGN NATIONALS seeking employment in the Philippines shall obtain an employment permit from the Department of Labor and Employment and shall be subjected to a Labor Market Test based on non-availability of qualified and willing Filipino nationals.

States that foreign nationals issued employment permits shall transfer technology to Filipino understudies within a prescribed period.

Prohibits foreign national issued an employment permit to transfer to another job or change employer without prior approval of the Secretary of Labor and Employment. 
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NOGRALES, KARLO ALEXEI B., NOGRALES, JERICHO JONAS B., ANGARA-CASTILLO, BELLAFLOR J., TING, RANDOLPH S., GO, MARK O., MENDOZA, RAYMUND DEMOCRITO C., UNABIA, PETER &quot;SR. PEDRO&quot; M., VILLARIN, TOM S., TAMBUNTING, GUS S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-10-04</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Salo (000 2018-11-13)</td><td>2. Alonte (000 2018-11-13)</td><tr><td>3. Garcia (J.E.) (000 2018-11-13)</td><tr><td colspan=3>AUTHORS(Final/Third Reading) :</td></tr><tr><td width='%33'>1. Nograles (K.A.)</td><td width='33%'>2. Nograles (J.J.)</td><tr><td width='%33'>3. Angara-Castillo</td><td width='33%'>4. Ting</td><tr><td width='%33'>5. Go (M.)</td><td width='33%'>6. Mendoza</td><tr><td width='%33'>7. Unabia</td><td width='33%'>8. Villarin</td><tr><td width='%33'>9. Tambunting</td><td width='33%'>10. Belmonte (R.)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITTEE REPORT NO.&nbsp00883</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBMITTED ON 2018-10-04</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBMITTED BY:&nbspLABOR AND EMPLOYMENT</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>RECOMMENDATIONS:&nbspApproval in substitution of House Bills Numbered 277 and 710</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBSTITUTED BILLS:&nbspHB00277, HB00710</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON RULES ON 2018-10-08</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE INCLUDED IN OB:&nbsp2018-10-08</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE CALENDARED :&nbsp2018-10-08</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>SECOND READING INFORMATION</b><br /><tr><td colspan=3>PERIOD OF SPONSORSHIP :&nbsp2018-11-13</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SPONSORED BY :&nbsp Ting</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FINAL LIST OF AUTHORS :&nbspNograles (K.A.), Nograles (J.J.), Angara-Castillo, Ting, Go (M.), Mendoza, Unabia, Villarin, Tambunting